The paper discusses the use of deep learning models for de novo drug design, which falls under the intersection of computer science and chemistry. The proposed metric, Fr\'echet ChemNet distance (FCD), is based on a deep neural network called ChemNet, which was trained to predict drug activities. This suggests that the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the FCD metric is similar to the Fr\'echet Inception Distance (FID), which is a performance metric for comparing image generation methods, indicating a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) as well.
